CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 23, 1963, pg. 7, reads: "After Luncheon - The quintet was snapped by the photographer after the Awards Luncheon honoring the 'Woman of the Year" and runners-up at the Carlton House Hotel. Chatting together, left to right: Miss Jeanne Dix, the Rev. James B. Cayce, Mrs. Homer S. Brown, Mrs. Eric Springer and Joe Black, director of special markets for the Greyhound Corporation and luncheon host. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Jeanne Dix, Rev. James B. Cayce, Wilhelmina Byrd Brown, Cecile Springer, and Joe Black, posed in Carlton House Hotel for "Woman of the Year" luncheon
